me.cassayre.florian.hawk.report

Class Report

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.cassayre.florian.hawk.report.Report

  • public class Report
extends Object
    A report.

    Saves data about a Minecraft game (players, teams, damages, heals, events) and exports them into a JSON format that can be used to build an user-friendly report.

      • autoTrack

        public Report autoTrack(boolean autoTrack)
        Enables or disables auto-track of all players damages & heals. If disabled, you'll have to manually register damages & heals for them to be recorded.

        Parameters:

        public Report autoCollectPreviousStatistics(boolean autoCollectPreviousStatistics)

      • setWinners

        public Report setWinners(UUID... winnersUUIDs)
        Explicitly sets the winners of the game.

        If not set and enabled in the settings, winners will be calculated automatically based on who is still alive. This calculation assumes players only have one life. If it's not the case, you should specify explicitly the winners.

        Parameters:
        winnersUUIDs - The winners' UUID.
        Returns:
        Current instance, for method chaining.
